{"lemma":"بُرْقُعَيْ","slug":"بُرْقُعَيْ","root":"ب.ر.ق.ع","root_slug":"ب-ر-ق-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ق-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2346","n2347","n2348","n2349"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cover"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"veil","examples":[{"text":"وَحَجَّبَتِ النَّوَى الظَّبَيَاتِ عَنِّي / فَسَاعَدَتِ الْبَرَاقِعَ وَٱلْحِجَالَا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"yashmak"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"curtain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hooded-horse blanket"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to envelop"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cover"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to veil"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enshroud"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to conceal"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wear feminine clothing"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be effeminate, to be a catamite"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ب ر ق ع (b r q ʕ), originally referring to a blaze or patch on a face of a horse near its eyes, then to a hooded-horse blanket for its covering of the same places; by extension any covering. Connected to the root ر ق ع (r q ʕ), meaning \"to patch\", \"to cover with fabric\", \"to adjoin patches like a quilt\", \"an odd patch or mark of a different color\"; the four-letter root being augmented potentially with بِ (bi, “with”) in the sense of \"a horse with a patch (on its face)\"."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2346","headword_ar":"بُرْقَعٌ","root":"brqE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2347","headword_ar":"بُرْقُعٌ","root":"brqE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroqaEN","text_ar":"بُرْقَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, Msb, K ,) but some disallow this latter, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroquwEN","text_ar":"بُرْقُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, S, K,) but AHát disallows this, as well as the second, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing pertaining to women and to horses or similar beasts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to horses or similar beasts and to the women of the Arabs of the desert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing with which a woman veils her face;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having in it two holes for the eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small piece of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rag, pierced for the eyes, worn by horses or similar beasts and by the women of the Arabs of the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) [or, accord. to the general fashion of the present time,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long  strip of cotton or other cloth, black, blue, or of some other colour, or white, concealing the whole of the face of the woman wearing it, except the eyes, and reaching nearly to the feet, suspended at the top by a narrow band, or other fastening, which passes up the middle of the forehead, and which is sewed, as are also the two upper corners, to a band which is tied round the head, beneath the head-veil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see my “ Manners and Customs of the Modern Egyptians, ” ch. i.:)] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroqaEapN","text_ar":"بُرْقَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", if correct, is a more particular term: (Mgh:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAqiEu","text_ar":"بَرَاقِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, Msb.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqaAbN","text_ar":"نِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlburoquEu","text_ar":"البُرْقُعُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The curtain of the door of the Kaabeh."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biroqiEu","text_ar":"بِرْقِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["IAar","S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n2348","headword_ar":"بِرْقَعُ","root":"brqE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2349","headword_ar":"بِرْقَعُ","root":"brqE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, * TA,) imperfectly decl., (S, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biroqaEu","text_ar":"بِرْقَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, Az, Ibn-'Abbád,) of a rare form, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijoraE","text_ar":"هِجْرَع"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, Az, *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbiroqiEu","text_ar":"البِرْقِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlburoquEu","text_ar":"البُرْقُعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) but perhaps this last is a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biroqaEu","text_ar":"بِرْقَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heaven,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seventh heaven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AAF, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fourth heaven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Az, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first heaven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lowest heaven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"IDrd says, so they assert; and in like manner says"},{"kind":"page_break","n":193},{"kind":"text","text":"IF; and he says, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative, the radical letters being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r q E","text_ar":"ر ق ع"},{"kind":"text","text":", for every heaven is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyEN","text_ar":"رَقِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the heavens [together] are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroqiEapN","text_ar":"اَرْقِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or the lowest heaven is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aqiyEu","text_ar":"الرَّقِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadirN","text_ar":"سَدِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroqaEapN","text_ar":"بُرْقَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroquEN","text_ar":"بُرْقُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroquwEN","text_ar":"بُرْقُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroquEN","text_ar":"بُرْقُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Fr","AAF","K","Lth","Az"]}]}}